      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, we're looking at a new compliance proposal for the Q3 rollout. The board wants to implement a mandatory 'Human Oversight Layer' where a diverse committee of underwriters reviews all denied mortgage applications to ensure we aren't missing any nuances or showing systemic bias. Can you run a quick analysis on how much this human intervention might impact the precision of our current automated scoring model?",
